<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1322,1593,1859]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,443,1593,1619]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 14.0–18.0 mm. Forewing ground color is brown with basal, median, and subterminal areas cream. Orbicular and reniform spots are gray outlined in cream. Main wing veins (R. M, and Anal) are highlighted gray. Hindwing is dirty white with costa, outer margin, and veins gray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1322,1593,1859]" box="[312,624,1753,1779]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
